			<h1><em>Eastern Echo</em> is very different from the earlier four-page newletters published at Eastern State Penitentiary.</h1>
			<h1>Printed on modern equipment, it was a color magazine written, edited, and designed by incarcerated men for national circulation.</h1>
		</div>
