	<div class="item">
			<h2>Because it was written for a national audience, including those untouched by the prison system, it includes a wide range of articles.</h2>
	</div>
	<div class="item">
			<p>Not only prison news but crossword puzzles, book reviews, poems, and longer essays on topics like rehabilitation and vocational training appear in its pages. Scholars outside the prison, like the sociologist and prison reform advocate Dr. Negley K. Teeters, sometimes published essays in <em>Eastern Echo</em> as well. Often the magazine attempts to share with a general audience what the experience of incarceration is like through art, stories, and opinion pieces.</p> 
	</div>
